history.content:
Come out to Launchpad’s Fall 2021 Final Showcase to see what our project teams have been working on this semester! We’ll be in the Wozniak Lounge on Thursday, 12/9 from 11-1 PM – and we’ll have free food 

Here are some short snippets about our projects; at the showcase you’ll have the chance to see some projects in action, talk to the project members, and ask any questions you have about their work!

––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

 PROJECTS 

 Scribe: Few-shot learning handwriting styles with meta learning, and then generating similar handwritten text with GANs.

 Phodexr: Enable semantic search through images and other mediums in a zero-shot manner with CLIP.
Inflection: Voice conversion for personalizing chat bots to speak in any speaker’s voice.

 Lucinator: Build a production-ready virtual assistant with industrial pipelines and custom functionalities.

 Duet: Use VQ-VAEs to convert a music snippet to the style of another music file.

 Lightspeed (client project): Use style transfer to augment cellular extractions to detect abnormalities solely through computation.

RSVP on the Facebook event here.
